  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into chips and add to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Strip your <strong>rosemary leaves</strong> from their stems and chop them roughly, discard the stems, then sprinkle the<strong> chopped rosemary </strong>all over the chips and put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until crisp – these are your <strong>rosemary chips</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1679572701407-x200.jpg",
