    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and <strong>tomato paste </strong>to the pot<strong> </strong>and cook for 30 secs further</p><p>Add 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[130ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[150ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> with your <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong> and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, cook for 5-6 min or until the tomatoes have broken down and it's reduced to a ketchup-like consistency – this is your <strong>tomato relish</strong></p>",
